  "@type": "Capability",
  "critical": false,
  "description": "Raising domesticated sheep (Ovis aries) for wool, mutton, and dairy. Sheep produce 2-5 kg fleece per shearing (60-70% clean fiber yield), reach slaughter weight at 4-6 months, and provide nitrogen-rich manure (0.7% N fresh weight). Wool is the primary fiber for textiles before cotton and synthetics.",
  "early_win": true,
  "early_win_note": "Sheep produce wool within the first year, enabling textile production. Fast reproduction (twins common) builds flock quickly.",
